# Auto-commit after changes

After completing any coding task (fixes, features, refactors, or builds), run:

```bash
git add . && git commit -m "Brief description of what was done"
```

Use a descriptive commit message that summarizes the changes (e.g. "Fix privacy lock back navigation", "Add metrics line chart", "Add notifications module").
